Executive Slide Deck Requirements
Your presentation is intended for Big Mountain Resort management, so the tone and structure should be clear, concise, and decision‑focused. Follow the steps below to build your executive‑level slide deck.
---
1. Problem Identification (1–2 slides)
• Clearly state the business problem Big Mountain Resort is facing.
• Highlight why the issue matters (financial impact, customer experience, competitive pressure).
• Include any relevant visuals that support the problem statement (e.g., distribution plots, comparisons).
---
2. Recommendation and Key Findings (1 slide)
• Present your primary recommendation up front.
• Summarize the most important insights that support your recommendation.
• Keep this slide high‑level and executive‑friendly.
---
3. Modeling Results and Analysis (3–4 slides)
• Show the results of your predictive modeling.
• Include the scenario analyses you ran (e.g., changes in runs, vertical drop, chairlifts, snow‑making).
• Use charts to illustrate ticket price changes and revenue impacts.
• Explain what the model suggests and how the features influence outcomes.
• Keep explanations clear and avoid technical jargon unless necessary.
---
4. Summary and Conclusion (1 slide)
• Reinforce your recommendation.
• Summarize the expected benefits for Big Mountain Resort.
• Close with a clear call to action or next steps.
---
Submission Instructions
• Ensure your slide deck’s share settings allow anyone with the link to view.
• Add your completed slide deck to your Guided Capstone folder in your GitHub repository.
• Submit the link to the folder as required.
